org.activebpel.rt.bpel.server.addressing
Class AePartnerAddressing

java.lang.Object
  org.activebpel.rt.bpel.server.addressing.AePartnerAddressing
All Implemented Interfaces:
IAePartnerAddressing
public class AePartnerAddressing
extends java.lang.Object
implements IAePartnerAddressing

The partner addressing layer is responsible for providing endpoint references for each of the partners that the business process interacts with. The endpoint data either exists as part of the deployment descriptor, as part of the message context, or from a partner definition object.

getReplyAddressing

public IAeAddressingHeaders getReplyAddressing(IAeWsAddressingHeaders aSource,
                                               java.lang.String aAction)
                                        throws AeBusinessProcessException
Description copied from interface: IAePartnerAddressing
Creates the required WS-Addressing headers for a response message, Determines the proper reply destination endpoint as follows: If the wsa Fault action is specified, the FaultTo endpoint is used, if available. If present, the ReplyTo header is used. If ReplyTo is unavailable, use the From header If neither ReplyTo nor From are available, default to the wsa anonymous role If the request contains a MessageId, the required RelatesTo header is included with a RelationshipType of wsa:Reply The From endpoint is the endpoint that was invoked

Specified by:
getReplyAddressing in interface IAePartnerAddressing
Parameters:
aSource - addressing headers from a request
aAction - response action to use
Returns:
The WS-Addressing headers for the response
Throws:
AeBusinessProcessException

Description copied from interface: IAePartnerAddressing
Reads a static endpoint reference encoded within the element. This is broken out from the deployment reader in the event that we ever move away from WS-Addressing, which is a possibility until WS-Addressing becomes an open source standard. We may need to have pluggable support for the xml formatted endpoint reference objects.

readFromContext

public IAeEndpointReference readFromContext(javax.xml.rpc.handler.soap.SOAPMessageContext aContext)
                                     throws AeBusinessProcessException
Description copied from interface: IAePartnerAddressing
If the partner link's endpoint source is set to "invoker" then the code will attempt to extract an IAeEndpointReference object from the metadata in the SOAPMessageContext. Currently, this is limited to extracting WS-Addressing compliant SOAP headers from a SOAPMessageContext. This gets called from the web service handler since that's the layer that has access to the context. Called from the deployment descriptor if the source type for the partner link was set to "invoker".

Description copied from interface: IAePartnerAddressing
If the endpoint source for the partner link was set to principal then the addressing layer obtains the endpoint reference data from the principal's provisioning data. Called indirectly from the engine (through the deployment descriptor) during the queueing of any receive data.
